ul.li:
Ignore properties - Here you can type comma separated patterns that match the names of CSS properties that will be ignored at validation. As wildcards you can use:
* to match any string;
? to match any character.

Recognize browser CSS extensions (applies also to content
          completion) - If checked,  recognizes (no validation is
        performed) browser-specific CSS properties. The Content Completion
          Assistant lists these properties at the end of its list, prefixed with the
        following particles:

-moz- for Mozilla;

-ms- for Internet Explorer;

-o- for Opera;

-webkit- for Safari/Webkit.
